title:Lentil Soup
ingredients:2 celery ribs, sliced//
1 medium onion, chopped//
1 garlic clove, minced//
2 tablespoons butter//
6 cups water//
1 can (28 ounces) diced tomatoes, undrained//
3/4 cup dry lentils//
3/4 cup pearl barley//
2 tablespoons chicken bouillon granules//
1/2 teaspoon dried oregano//
1/2 teaspoon dried rosemary, crushed//
1/4 teaspoon pepper//
1 cup sliced carrots//
1 cup swiss cheese, optional
instructions:In Dutch oven or soup kettle, saute celery, onion, and garlic in butter until tender.//
Add water, tomatoes, lentils, barley, bouillon, oregano, rosemary, and pepper.//
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.//
Cover ad simmer for 40 minutes until lentils are almost tender.//
Add carrots.//
simmer for 15 minutes until carrots are tender.//
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.